Issues.Body:
* .NET Core Version: 3.1.100
* Have you experienced this same bug with .NET Framework?: Yes

**Problem description:**
I want to use 100% scale to design UI in the winform designer, my screen resolution is 5120 * 1080 (200% scale);
Now a `Size` property 1000 * 800 is actually 500 * 400;
![size](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18641363/70417368-0a678c00-1a9c-11ea-8643-9aa5775c7f34.jpg)

If you let VS start at 100% scale [disable-dpi-awareness](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/designers/disable-dpi-awareness?view=vs-2019) will make VS less clear;
I very much hope that the winform designer can run at 100% scale, and F5 runing will not affect DPI scaling;
Just like WPF;

Thanks!
